        "text": "If |n/5k| ≤ 3, then the last term in the above sum has 5-valuation -k, since 11, 12, 1 each have valuation 0; on the other hand, all other terms must have 5valuation strictly larger than -k. It follows that H, has 5-valuation exactly —k; in particular, H, has nonnegative 5-valuation in this case if and only if k = 0, i.e., n = 1,2, or 3.",
