        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "It is clear that 120 = 124 = 0 (mod 25); hence if |n/5k-1| equals 20 or 24, then the second-to-last term of the above sum (if it exists) has valuation at least -k 3). The third-to-last term (if it exists) is of the form 1,/5k-2 , so that the sum of the last term and the third to last term takes the form (I, + 1/12) /5k-2. Since I, can be congruent only to 0,1, or -1 (mod 5), and 1/12 = 3 (mod 5), we conclude that the sum of the last term and third-to-last term has valuation -(k - 2), while all other terms have valuation strictly higher. Hence H, has nonnegative 5-valuation in this case only when k ≤ 2, leading to the values n = 4 (arising from k = 0), 20,24 (arising from k = 1 and |n/5k-1J = 20 and 24 resp.), 101, 102, 103, and 104 (arising from k = 2, (n/5k-1| = 20) and 120, 121, 122, 123, and 124 (arising from k = 2, In/5k-'J = 24).",
