        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Finally, suppose |n/5kJ= 4 and |n/5k-1] = 21, 22, or 23. Then as before, the first condition implies that the last term of the sum in (*) has valuation - (k - 2), while the second condition implies that the second-tolast term in the same sum has valuation - (k - 1). Hence all terms in the sum (*) have 5-valuation strictly higher than -(k - 1), except for the second-to-last term, and therefore Hn has 5-valuation - (k - 1) in this case. In particular, H, is integral (mod 5) in this case if and only if k ≤ 1, which gives the additional values n = 21, 22, and 23.",
